summary:
Goal-Oriented | Passionate | Self-Resilient | Open-Minded

Four words that describe who I am.

Thank you for visiting my LinkedIn profile. My name is Adelaide Aurore Djoumkam. I recently graduated with a Bachelor in Business Administration in International Business at Fontys University of Applied Sciences in Venlo, the Netherlands. 

In the first 2 years of my study I learned about different aspects within international business, where I applied the theory of courses in project with international project groups. The third year of my studies contained a minor and an internship. In February 2020 I did a minor in Strategies for Innovative Communication by the Fontys University of Applied Sciences in Eindhoven. Here I learned strategic advice in the areas of branding, PR and marketing. 

In the second half of the third year, I started my internship at John Deere Fabriek Horst, the Netherlands. Here I was a supply chain intern. In the last year, I did a graduation internship at DAF Trucks Eindhoven PACCAR Parts Purchasing department. 

I specialized in supply chain in my final year of study.  I am currently open for a job preferably within the domain of supply chain management/ logistics or Customer support. I am currently undergoing Lean Six Sigma training at Lean 6 sigma productivity Solutions for the Green Belt.

I am a results-oriented and highly motivated individual financially aware with strong analytical skills with experience working within a team. I have good verbal and non-verbal communication skills seeking to put my theoretical knowledge into practice geared toward the attainment of the company objectives. 

Aside from that, my future plans are developing myself both professionally and personal level. I would like to expand my knowledge in Dutch after which I would like to learn other languages.

I will love to hear from you! Should you have any offers or questions please send me a text or mail!

Thank you
